Questions FARM LOAN BOARD—BRITISH COLUMBIA

Mr. Pearkes: 1. At what points in Canada are branches of the farm loan board located?

2. Who is responsible for the operation of the board on Vancouver island, British Columbia?

3. How many applications for loans were made from British Columbia last year?

4. How many of these were approved?

Mr. _Belzile:

1. New Westminster, British Columbia; Edmonton, Alberta; Regina, Saskatchewan; Winnipeg, Manitoba; Toronto, Ontario; Que- bec, Quebec; Saint John, New Brunswick; Halifax, Nova Scotia; Charlottetown, Prince Edward Island.

2. Mr. W. S. Palmer, Branch Manager, Canadian farm loan board, New Westminster, B.C.

3. 229.

4. Ninety-one have been approved for loan and 28 were still pending as of February 11, 1949. Of the 28 pending applications, 17 of the securities offered have not as yet been appraised.
